The mention of an algebraic theory suggests a focus on mathematics and theoretical computer science, which could fall under the categories of cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). Finally, the use of the Karatsuba multiplication algorithm for numerical analysis suggests a possible connection to the category of cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
